<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; CARTER PROVIDES ANOTHER CHALLENGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After surviving the challenge of Washington's Napoleon Kaufman in its opener, 
USC's defense will face another Saturday against Penn State at State College, 
Pa. 
</P>
<P>
 While USC "limited" the explosive Kaufman to 156 yards rushing, with a longest 
run of 21 yards, in a 24-17 victory, Penn State junior Ki-Jana Carter ran for 
210 yards and three touchdowns in a 56-3 victory over Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of Carter's runs went for 80 and 62 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 A year ago, in a 21-20 victory over USC, Carter carried 21 times for 104 
yards, with a longest run of 15 yards. On a day when the Trojans rushed for 
only 34 yards, the 5-foot-10, 212-pounder from Westerville, Ohio, was part of a 
Penn State offense that ran for 282 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Carter gained 1,026 yards last season, becoming Penn State's first 1,000-yard 
rusher since Blair Thomas in 1989. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
