<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NATION; OFFENSIVE COACH TORPEDOED 
BY NAVY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Navy offensive coordinator Greg Briner was fired in the aftermath of the 
Midshipmen's 56-14 season-opening loss to San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach George Chaump said Briner was fired for what he called "philosophical 
differences in running a football program." 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego State outgained Navy, 503 yards to 232. 
</P>
<P>
 Briner came to the Naval Academy last season after three years at Marshall. 
</P>
<P>
 Briner helped lead the Thundering Herd to the Division I-AA national 
championship in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Briner was a quarterback and defensive back at USC, where he was a member of a 
team that reached the Rose Bowl in 1969. 
</P>
</TEXT>
