<P>
 On the surface, it looks like a rebuilding year for the Cougars. Lots of holes 
being filled with inexperienced players, some up from a 7-3 freshman team. But 
if not dominant, the Cougars will at least be dangerous. MacKenzie makes Patton 
bubble with enthusiasm. MacKenzie is big, strong and fast, three things coaches 
tend to like in a tailback. All he lacks is varsity experience. He has a big 
offensive line to run behind, led by Honeycutt, who was underrated last season. 
Purvis is a solid tight end. The defense has more questions. Grigas is the only 
returning starter. He's good, but he can't be everywhere. 
</P>
