<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL Jim Barnett: 71-27-2 03,20,05,05 RETURNING STARTERS 
OFF DEF 4 6 04,26,05,05,05 TOP RETURNERS OFF DEF YR Jake Anderson, 5-9, 170 -- 
DB Sr. Zane Champion, 6-3, 235 OL -- Sr. Chris Clayton, 5-10, 180 -- DB Sr. 
Chad Collins, 6-9, 165 QB -- Sr. Laquent Fobbs, 5-9, 160 WR -- Sr. Larry 
Harper, 5-8, 165 RB -- Sr. Todd Haynes, 5-7, 170 RB -- Sr. Rob Jacobs, 6-3 1/2, 
275 OL DL Sr. Bobby Johnson, 5-10, 160 RB -- Sr. Randy Ortiz, 5-8, 155 -- DB 
Sr. J.C. Pintsak, 6-1, 170 QB -- Sr. Jeremy Taylor, 6-1, 205 -- LB Sr. 
04,24,05,05,05 TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR Brian Carter, 5-8, 155 -- DB Jr. 
OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills won the Division VIII title last season and now finds itself 
playing in a Division I league. Tough break. The Mustangs probably don't have 
what it takes to challenge for the league championship this season, but they 
should be in the running for a playoff spot. Collins threw for 903 yards and 
seven touchdowns during the regular season, but at the moment Pintsak is the 
starter. "The one thing I will say is we have the best two quarterbacks in the 
(Orange) County," Barnett said. "Our two are better than any other two at any 
school." From there, it gets a little thin. Fobbs is a dangerous receiver. He 
caught 22 passes during the regular season a year ago. Jacobs can open some 
holes, but who will run through them is the question. Harper, Haynes and 
Johnson are in contention. Taylor is the team's best defensive player. Carter 
is good enough that he would have been on the varsity last season if he had 
been old enough. 
</P>
