<P>
 Denny takes over this program divided. Turmoil has hurt the Diablos for the 
past few seasons. There have been plenty of distractions, from coaches who were 
fired to coaches who were hired, not to mention public disputes about their 
unofficial devil mascot. But hope abounds under Denny, a Mission Viejo 
assistant the past five seasons. Actually, if the off-the-field and 
behind-closed-doors problems are resolved, the Diablos could have a good 
season. Moherman was a find at quarterback. He drove the Diablos to a field 
goal against Mater Dei on his first varsity series. Moherman threw two 
touchdown passes in a 42-0 victory over Dana Hills. Keneley is a force on 
defense. He was a first-team all-league selection a year ago. The offense and 
defensive lines are solid, but skill position players lack experience. 
Somewhere, the Diablos must find a running game. But compared to the program's 
past woes, that should be child's play. 
