<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; STANFORD BEATS TITANS IN SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stanford scored with about four minutes left and Cal State Fullerton missed a 
chance to tie in the closing seconds of the Cardinal's 3-2 victory in a Reebok 
Classic men's soccer game Monday at Titan Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans (1-1) are the seventh-ranked team in the nation.Unranked Stanford 
is 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 All the scoring came in the final 15 minutes. Stanford took the lead, 3-2, 
when Carmen D'Onofrio scored on a free kick in the 86th minute. The Titans' 
Joey Franchino had a chance to tie it, but his shot hit the side post just 
before time ran out. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Collins had two goals for Stanford, the second coming in the 77th minute 
and putting the Cardinal ahead, 2-1. Fullerton's Brad Wilson tied it about 
seven minutes later. Adrian Cortes scored the other Fullerton goal. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA beat Cal State Sacramento, 5-0, also Monday and won the tournament with a 
2-0 record. 
</P>
<P>
 In the women's Reebok Classic: 
</P>
<P>
 CS Fullerton 2, Pacific 0 -- Amber Dickey scored a goal in each half as the 
host Titans recorded their first victory over a Division I opponent in the 
two-year history of the program.  
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Baptist 1, Chapman 0 -- Pat Smith scored on a penalty kick with less than 
two minutes remaining for visiting Cal Baptist (1-0). Chapman goalkeeper Craig 
Bennett set up the penalty kick when he was called for a pushing in the penalty 
box during a Cal Baptist free kick. 
</P>
