<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MUCHA WINS TOURNAMENT AFTER DAVIES FALTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Barb Mucha took advantage of Laura Davies' front-nine collapse Monday and 
posted a one-shot victory over Kim Shipman in the State Farm Rail Classic in 
Springfield, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
 Mucha shot a final-round five-under 67 and finished the 54-hole tournament 
with a 13-under 203 total. Shipman closed with a 69. 
</P>
<P>
 Davies had a four-shot lead entering the final round. She missed short birdie 
putts on the first two holes and another on No. 4. She found the water on Nos. 
6, 7 and 8 and finished the front side at five-over 41. She ended tied for 14th 
at 208 after closing with a 77. Baseball  
</P>
<P>
 Former Detroit Tiger and Dodgers pitcher Hank Aguirre, who moved from baseball 
to the auto industry where he created jobs for hundreds of Latinos, died of 
prostate cancer at his home in Bloomfield, Mich. He was 62. 
</P>
<P>
 Aguirre, a three-time All-Star who grew up in Azuza, began an auto parts 
manufacturing company called Mexican Industries, and employed 800 Latino 
workers from southwestern Detroit. 
</P>
<P>
 Aguirre was 75-72 with a 3.25 earned-run average in 16 years. His best season 
was 1962, when he had a 16-8 record and a league-leading 2.21 ERA for the 
Tigers. 
</P>
<P>
 Aguirre also was known for being one of baseball's worst hitters. He batted 
.085 (33 for 388), with no home runs, and was two for 75 (.027) in 1962. Boxing 
 
</P>
<P>
 Ike Williams, lightweight champion of the world in the late-1940s, one of 
boxing's golden eras, was found dead in his Wilshire district apartment. He was 
71. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are investigating Williams' death, a spokesman said. Witnesses said a 
television was missing from the apartment. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams was inducted into the International Boxing Hall of Fame in 1978 and 
had a professional record of 123-19-5, with 60 knockouts. 
</P>
<P>
 He won the lightweight title in 1945 by defeating Juan Zorita, who stayed in 
touch with Williams and was one of the first people to discover Williams' body 
Monday. Williams lost the title in 1951 to James Carter. Soccer  
</P>
<P>
 A top British soccer player has been charged with murder, police in the 
northwestern English city of Liverpool said. 
</P>
<P>
 James Kelly, 21, who plays for the first-division Wolverhampton Wanderers, was 
to appear in court today with his brother John, 22, and another man. 
</P>
<P>
 The charge follows the death of Peter Dunphy, 26, whose body was found outside 
a hotel in Liverpool on Sunday. Miscellany  
</P>
<P>
 Two-time professional world cycling champion Gianni Bugno was suspended for 
two years because he tested positive for an excessive amount of caffeine after 
a minor Italian road race last month. 
</P>
<P>
 Connie Kalitta, Cruz Pedregon, Warren Johnson and David Schultz each won 
titles at the 40th annual NHRA U.S. Nationals in Clermont, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
 McLaren Peugeot could be banned from the rest of the Formula One season after 
being called to appear before the sport's ruling body, the International 
Automobile Federation, for using an illegal gearbox at the San Marino Grand 
Prix. 
</P>
<P>
 Finland's J.J. Lehto will replace suspended Formula One standings leader 
Michael Schumacher at the wheel of in his Benetton-Ford at the Italian Grand 
Prix on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
