<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: STORE OPERATOR IS ARRESTED IN SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Moorpark liquor store operator who became fed up with a man trying to sell 
electronics in front of his shop was arrested after he shot at the man to force 
him to leave, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Abdulrahman Barakat, 31, was arrested Saturday outside his store in the 400 
block of High Street in Moorpark after he allegedly shot at Juan Carlos 
Salazar, 26, of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Barakat asked Salazar to leave the property, and the two men began arguing, 
according to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Barakat went into his store and retrieved a semiautomatic pistol, 
then shot at Salazar as he was running away. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the incident, police said. Barakat was arrested on 
suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon. 
</P>
<P>
 More than a year ago, Barakat was the victim of a stabbing at his store, which 
has been owned by his family for more than 24 years. In that incident, Barakat 
was attacked after he refused to cash an income-tax refund check for the 
assailant. 
</P>
<P>
 Following Saturday's shooting, Barakat was released from Ventura County Jail 
on $5,000 bail. He could not be reached for comment, and a woman working at the 
store declined to discuss the shooting. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
