<TEXT>
<P>
 An 81-year-old Oxnard man was seriously injured Monday when his car struck a 
telephone pole in Oxnard, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fidel M. Solano was driving south on Vineyard Avenue near Stroube Street at 
about 8:52 a.m. when the car left the road for unknown reasons and smashed into 
a telephone pole, Officer Timothy Lumas said. The crash, which sheared the pole 
off at the base, left Solano with massive internal injuries, including a 
punctured lung, Lumas said. 
</P>
