<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 25 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 13. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 324. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 345. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $110.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $212.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: Acting commissioner Bud Selig met with Labor Secretary 
Robert Reich in Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "On this Labor Day, there's still time for them to go back to 
work and finish the best baseball season in 50 years -- and I hope they will." 
</P>
<P>
 -- President Clinton 
</P>
