<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOCUS ON ENTERTAINMENT STOCKS: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Market trends: Microsoft Corp. was the volume leader in Monday's trading. 
Trimark Holdings Inc. announced a fourth-quarter profit of $616,000 on sales of 
$20.9 million, compared to a year-ago profit of $1.4 million on sales of $19.8 
million. The company said it experienced higher acquisition costs in fiscal 
1994. 
</P>
