<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA HABRA FULLERTON; FORUMS TO FEATURE COUNCIL CANDIDATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four of the five candidates in the La Habra City Council race and three of the 
25 candidates in the Fullerton election will discuss why they are running for 
office and answer questions from the audience Wednesday at the Kling Center in 
La Mirada. 
</P>
<P>
 The La Habra candidates scheduled to be present are Rose Espinoza, Kent 
Roberts, Dorothy Rush and Paul Thornburg. 
</P>
<P>
 From Fullerton, the candidates expected to attend are Jack Dean, Conrad 
DeWitte and Jacob Spaargaren. 
</P>
<P>
 Zona Neighbors, a La Habra resident organizing the event, which is sponsored 
by United We Stand America, said only a few candidates were invited because the 
Kling Center is too small to accommodate all candidates. 
</P>
<P>
 One candidate, La Habra Mayor David M. Cheverton, was not invited because "he 
already gets a lot of public exposure," Neighbors said. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is good exposure for the people who don't get exposure," she added. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited to the forum at the center, which is at 12900 Bluefield 
in La Mirada. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors said another forum will be held before the October special election 
in Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 All candidates who were not invited to the September forum will be invited to 
speak at the next one, Neighbors said. MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
