<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; DRIVE-IN SITE SET FOR HOMES PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has approved a conceptual plan for Greystone developers to build a 
new gated community of 224 homes and condominiums in an area that once was home 
to the Drive-In Theatre on Lincoln Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The city had been working with another developer about two years ago, but that 
company failed to close a deal, Development Services Director Thomas Lynch 
said.The Greystone developers presented their plans to the city earlier this 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
 The 32-acre development will have 114 single-family homes and 110 detached 
condominiums. Residents will have a one-acre park and a swimming pool. The city 
would require a 2.2-acre park, but large lawns and walkways will provide six 
acres of open space, said Rick Warsinski, the assistant director of development 
services. 
</P>
<P>
 "We feel like this project is exactly what we wanted through the General 
Plan," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilwoman Donna L. Chessen said she liked the development but was concerned 
about one swimming pool serving hundreds of homes. 
</P>
<P>
 Larry Webb, Greystone's division president, said the 25-foot rear yards allows 
ample space for private pools and many would probably be built by individual 
homeowners. The price of condos will begin in the lower $200,000 range and 
private homes will be closer to $300,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Donald L. Bone also said he approved of the project but was concerned 
about the lack of parking on the private streets. 
</P>
<P>
 The project should go to a public hearing within a month or two, Warsinski 
said.LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</TEXT>
