SUN VALLEY MAN DROWNS AT LAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Sun Valley man who could not swim drowned here Monday after he waded about 
20 feet offshore and his friends lost sight of him, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Alfonzo Figueroa, 24, was pulled from the water about 5:20 p.m. by his 
friends, who thought he was joking and laughed when he began to flail about in 
the water, said Los Angeles County Sheriff's Deputy Frank Juarez. 
</P>
