</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR KILLED IN TRUCKEE PLANE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four people were killed when a single-engine plane crashed shortly after 
takeoff Monday from the Truckee Tahoe Airport and burst into flames, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We know nothing as yet about the victims or the plane's destination," said 
Bill Chilcott, president of the airport board. 
</P>
<P>
 He said the Cessna 172-RG crashed at 10:15 a.m. about 700 feet from the end of 
the runway. 
</P>
<P>
 He declined to speculate on the cause of the crash, but said it sparked a 
small brush fire that was quickly put out by crews. 
</P>
<P>
 "The airport emergency teams were out there immediately, but there was no 
chance to save the people on board the plane," Chilcott said. 
</P>
<P>
 Federal Aviation Administration investigators were en route to the scene to 
begin their investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 Skies were clear and winds were light when the plane went down, officials 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
